Description: Wall sherd of East Greek pottery cup; fine orange clay with some silver mica; glaze mostly fired red-brown; interior glazed; exterior: cream slip, red paint; bits of verticals preserved in reserved zone at top, glazed below; inscription cut on interior.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of Apollo (Naukratis) (said to be)
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.368)
